main event: Four circular, penny-sized white objects were observed in East Rochester, New Hampshire for forty-five seconds.
interesting points: The observation was made by a civilian looking out of a window.
The objects formed a straight line and then a square before fading out and reappearing.
The conclusion reached was that the objects were possibly balloons or aircraft.
The report includes detailed information about wind speed and direction during the observation.
The witness communicated the sighting to the authorities by telling Concord to relay the message.
